oks and Heidegger's metapolitics, even as he uncovers an ethical dimension within Heidegger that pervades his reading of poetry. Throughout all of these various stages on Heidegger's thought path, Hölderlin remains the poet who poetizes the possibility of finding our lost home amidst the homelessness brought about in the epoch of technological thinking.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aNational socialism. 0aPolitical sciencexPhilosophy. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aHistory : History. 4aHistory : Holocaust Studies. 4aLiterature : Literature. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 70(DE-588)4049716-10(DE-627)1046751520(DE-576)209083182aRezeption2gnd7(dpeaa)DE-631 7aPHILOSOPHY / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2022z978311149185140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848814140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438488141423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438488141/original  a978-3-11-149185-1  SUNY Press eBook Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles